article.description: — Tyler Stephenson-Moore scored 22 points as Stony Brook beat Hampton 93-73 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Stephenson-Moore scores 22 as Stony Brook downs Hampton 93-73
article.linkText: Stephenson-Moore scores 22 as Stony Brook downs Hampton 93-73
article.story: STONY BROOK, N.Y. -- — Tyler Stephenson-Moore scored 22 points as Stony Brook beat Hampton 93-73 on Thursday night. Stephenson-Moore added three steals for the Seawolves (14-12, 7-6 Coastal Athletic Association). Keenan Fitzmorris added 20 points while going 7 of 10 and 6 of 6 from the free-throw line, and he also had six rebounds. Toby Onyekonwu scored 13 points. Andre Snoddy had eight points, 12 rebounds and five assists. Kyrese Mullen led the way for the Pirates (5-21, 0-13) with 23 points. Jordan Nesbitt added 20 points, four assists and two steals for Hampton. Jerry Deng also had 10 points and seven rebounds. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
